But we will take it for granted, however, that what they ſaid was true, not becauſe they ſaid it, but becauſe the experience of all Ages doth confirm it, and concur with it: So that a little Acquaintance with Books and the World will prove the Obſervation which we ground upon this Text;



                     Doct.That it is, and always hath been, the Lot of Chriſt's Holy Religion, to be every where ſpoken againſt. Or thus:


That true Chriſtianity hath all along met with a great deal of Oppoſition and Contradiction in this World.
